
Overview of verb lurk

The verb lurk has 3 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (8) lurk, skulk -- (lie in wait, lie in ambush, behave in a sneaky and secretive manner)
2. (1) loiter, lounge, footle, lollygag, loaf, lallygag, hang around, mess about, tarry, linger, lurk, mill about, mill around -- (be about; "The high school students like to loiter in the Central Square"; "Who is this man that is hanging around the department?")
3. ambush, scupper, bushwhack, waylay, lurk, ambuscade, lie in wait -- (wait in hiding to attack)
